name: methane, dibromofluoro-
Reason: The basic unit, methane, has a melting point of -182 degrees Celsius. Each bromine atom contributes to a substantially higher melting point due to increased molecular weight and intermolecular forces (estimated at +50 degrees Celsius per bromine). The fluorine atom, being smaller than bromine, contributes less to the melting point (estimated at +10 degrees Celsius).
